2500|$|In April 2015, Corker's {{position}} on Iraq was that {{turmoil in the}} Middle East predated Barack Obama's presidency, and that by <b>invading</b> <b>Iraq</b> in 2003 the U.S. “took a big stick and beat a hornets’ nest”, unleashing rivalries that might take decades to resolve.|$|R
50|$|Mr Galloway Goes to Washington: the Brit who set Congress {{straight}} about Iraq is a 2005 book by British politician George Galloway. The book {{concerned the}} actions of the United States in <b>invading</b> <b>Iraq,</b> the fallout and Galloway's 2005 appearance before the US senate.|$|R
